	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Characters not referred to by name in the body of a screenplay tend to be credited under something other than a name. For example, if <em>All My Circuits</em> were real, it might officially credit &quot;Calculon's Butler&quot;. Likewise, BK in <em>Kill Bill Vol. 1</em> was referred to only as &quot;The Bride&quot;, except for a fleeting view of her real name on her ID that couldn't be easily perceived before the film's release on home video. (See <a href="https://allthetropes.org/wiki/No_Name_Given" class="postlink">&quot;No Name Given&quot; on All The Tropes</a>.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


